The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, October 30, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Oct. 29: Four people were injured, two of them critically, when a private bus lost control and climbed onto a footpath along Bidhan Sarani around 8 this morning.

 The bus on route 43/1, which lost control while speeding near Hedua, hit the pedestrians and rammed into a shop across the pavement. Two of them had to be admitted to RG Kar Medical College Hospital. 

 Calcutta: Police picked up five people from in front of Sreeram Arcade on Saturday for collecting money for the treatment of a child who did not exist. Puja Pal, Aparna Roy, Durga Sengupta, Debasish Bag and Arun Naskar confessed to their crime when the policemen on duty challenged them.




